ulnerability of 103 bird species native to the Brazilian Cerrado to changes in climate and land use projected for 2050, and found that the horned sungem is adaptable and comparatively insensitive to these threats. One of the criteria used was the dispersal ability (the bird's ability to move to new areas), which was estimated based on wing measurements. Together with another hummingbird, the frilled coquette, the horned sungem had the highest estimated dispersal ability of the studied species. References External links Photograph of a cup nest with eggs Photograph of a cup nest with two chicks Photograph of a female sitting in her nest Photograph of a female attending her chicks at the nest Photograph of a female feeding a juvenile", "shortSummary": "The horned sungem (Heliactin bilophus) is a species of hummingbird native to much of central Brazil and parts of Bolivia and Suriname. It p…", "locations": ["巴伊亞州", "弗里德里希·博伊厄", "昆拉德·雅各布·特明克", "玻利維亞", "蘇利南", "马拉尼昂州", "圣保罗州", "亚马孙州 (巴西)", "圣埃斯皮里图州", "森林砍伐", "阿馬帕州", "阿克里州", "里約熱內盧州", "Caatinga"], "habitats": ["稀树草原"], "lat": -12.0, "lng": -41.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Horned_Sungem%2C_Chapada_Diamantini%2C_Bahia_Brazil_%28cropped%29.jpg/960px-Horned_Sungem%2C_Chapada_Diamantini%2C_Bahia_Brazil_%28cropped%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-heliactin", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-heliactin-bilophus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-heliactin", "species": "taxonomy-species-heliactin-bilophus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 382.23, "y": 371.38, "z": 519.21}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-heliactin-bilophus", "name": "角蜂鸟", "latinName": "Heliactin bilophus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "角蜂鸟（Heliactin bilophus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当